<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>{{ title or "Audit Report" }}</title>
<style>
  @page {
    size: A4;
    margin: 15mm 16mm 18mm 16mm;
    @top-right {
      content: "CONFIDENTIAL";
      font-size: 7px;
      color: #cbd5e1;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }
    @bottom-center {
      content: "AuditForge — Page " counter(page) " of " counter(pages);
      font-size: 7.5px;
      color: #94a3b8;
    }
    @bottom-right {
      content: "{{ generated_at }}";
      font-size: 6.5px;
      color: #94a3b8;
    }
  }
  @page :first { @top-right { content: none; } @bottom-center { content: none; } @bottom-right { content: none; } }
  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 9.5px; color: #1e293b; line-height: 1.55; orphans: 3; widows: 3; }

  /* ── Cover page ── */
  .cover { text-align: center; padding: 80px 40px 50px; page-break-after: always; position: relative; }
  .cover::before { content: ''; display: block; width: 80px; height: 4px; background: linear-gradient(90deg, #1e40af, #3b82f6, #93c5fd); border-radius: 2px; margin: 0 auto 30px; }
  .cover .brand { font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 3px; text-transform: uppercase; color: #64748b; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .cover h1 { font-size: 24px; color: #0f172a; margin-bottom: 6px; font-weight: 700; }
  .cover .subtitle { font-size: 13px; color: #475569; margin-bottom: 30px; }
  .cover .meta-block { display: inline-block; text-align: left; border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0; padding-top: 16px; }
  .cover .meta-line { font-size: 10px; color: #334155; margin: 4px 0; }
  .cover .meta-line strong { color: #0f172a; min-width: 80px; display: inline-block; }
  .cover::after { content: ''; display: block; width: 60px; height: 3px; background: #3b82f6; border-radius: 2px; margin: 40px auto 0; }

  /* ── Headings with WeasyPrint PDF bookmarks ── */
  h2 {
    font-size: 13px; color: #1e40af; margin: 16px 0 8px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #dbeafe; padding-bottom: 4px; letter-spacing: 0.3px;
    bookmark-level: 1;
    bookmark-state: open;
  }
  h3 {
    font-size: 10.5px; color: #334155; margin: 10px 0 5px; font-weight: 600;
    bookmark-level: 2;
  }

  .section { margin-bottom: 14px; }

  /* Statistics cards */
  .stats { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .stat-card { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #eff6ff, #dbeafe); padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 6px; text-align: center; min-width: 80px; flex: 1; border: 1px solid #bfdbfe; }
  .stat-card .val { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: #1e40af; }
  .stat-card .lbl { font-size: 7px; color: #64748b; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; margin-top: 1px; }

  /* Compliance bar */
  .compliance-bar { height: 8px; background: #fee2e2; border-radius: 4px; overflow: hidden; margin: 6px 0; }
  .compliance-bar .fill { height: 100%; border-radius: 4px; }
  .compliance-bar .fill-good { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #22c55e, #16a34a); }
  .compliance-bar .fill-warn { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #f59e0b, #d97706); }
  .compliance-bar .fill-bad { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ef4444, #dc2626); }

  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 4px; font-size: 8.5px; }
  th, td { padding: 4px 6px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; text-align: left; }
  th { background: #f1f5f9; font-weight: 600; color: #334155; font-size: 8px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.3px; }
  tbody tr:nth-child(even) { background: #f8fafc; }

  .badge { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 8.5px; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; letter-spacing: 0.3px; }
  .sev-critical { background: #dc2626; }
  .sev-high { background: #ea580c; }
  .sev-medium { background: #d97706; color: #fff; }
  .sev-low { background: #2563eb; }
  .sev-informational { background: #6b7280; }
  .st-pass { background: #16a34a; }
  .st-fail { background: #dc2626; }
  .st-error { background: #7c3aed; }

  /* ── Enhanced finding cards ── */
  .finding-card { border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; border-radius: 6px; padding: 8px 10px; margin-bottom: 8px; page-break-inside: avoid; background: #fff; }
  .finding-card.sev-border-critical { border-left: 4px solid #dc2626; }
  .finding-card.sev-border-high { border-left: 4px solid #ea580c; }
  .finding-card.sev-border-medium { border-left: 4px solid #d97706; }
  .finding-card.sev-border-low { border-left: 4px solid #2563eb; }
  .finding-card.sev-border-informational { border-left: 4px solid #6b7280; }
  .finding-card .header { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 5px; padding-bottom: 4px; border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f5f9; }
  .finding-card .header .rule-id { font-weight: 700; font-size: 9.5px; color: #0f172a; }
  .finding-card p { margin: 2px 0; font-size: 8.5px; }
  .finding-card code { background: #f1f5f9; padding: 1px 4px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 8px; font-family: 'Consolas', 'Courier New', monospace; color: #334155; word-break: break-all; }
  .finding-card .field-label { font-weight: 600; color: #475569; display: inline-block; min-width: 70px; }
  /* Truncate long output values to keep cards compact */
  .finding-card .output-val { display: block; max-height: 60px; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; }
  .finding-card .output-val-full { display: block; max-height: none; }

  .ai-advice-box { background: #eff6ff; border-left: 3px solid #3b82f6; padding: 4px 8px; margin: 4px 0; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; font-size: 8.5px; }
  .eval-box { background: #f0fdf4; border-left: 3px solid #22c55e; padding: 4px 8px; margin: 4px 0; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; font-size: 8.5px; }
  .rationale-box { background: #fefce8; border-left: 3px solid #eab308; padding: 4px 8px; margin: 4px 0; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; font-size: 8.5px; }

  .passed-summary { margin-top: 8px; }
  .passed-summary li { margin-left: 18px; font-size: 9px; }

  .ai-summary { background: #eff6ff; border-left: 4px solid #1e40af; padding: 8px 12px; margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 9px; border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0; line-height: 1.6; }
  .ai-summary h2, .ai-summary h3 { font-size: 10px; color: #1e40af; margin: 8px 0 4px; border-bottom: none; bookmark-level: none; }
  .ai-summary p { margin: 4px 0; font-size: 9px; }
  .ai-summary ol, .ai-summary ul { margin: 4px 0 4px 18px; font-size: 9px; }
  .ai-summary li { margin-bottom: 2px; }
  .ai-summary strong { color: #0f172a; }

  /* ── Table of Contents ── */
  .toc { page-break-after: always; }
  .toc h2 { border-bottom: none; bookmark-level: none; }
  .toc-title { font-size: 16px; color: #1e40af; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 14px; border-bottom: 3px solid #1e40af; padding-bottom: 6px; }
  .toc-list { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  .toc-list li { padding: 4px 0; font-size: 9.5px; border-bottom: 1px dotted #cbd5e1; }
  .toc-list li a { color: #1e293b; text-decoration: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; }
  .toc-list li a::after { content: target-counter(attr(href), page); color: #64748b; font-weight: 600; }
  .toc-list li.toc-sub { padding-left: 18px; font-size: 10px; border-bottom: 1px dotted #e2e8f0; }
  .toc-list li.toc-sub a::after { font-weight: 400; }

  /* ── Severity group headers ── */
  .severity-group-header {
    margin: 12px 0 8px; padding: 6px 12px; border-radius: 5px;
    font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; page-break-after: avoid;
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
  }
  .severity-group-header.sev-bg-critical { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #dc2626, #b91c1c); }
  .severity-group-header.sev-bg-high { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ea580c, #c2410c); }
  .severity-group-header.sev-bg-medium { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706, #b45309); }
  .severity-group-header.sev-bg-low { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2563eb, #1d4ed8); }
  .severity-group-header.sev-bg-informational { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6b7280, #4b5563); }
  .severity-group-header .count-badge { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.25); padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 8.5px; }

  /* ── Section count badge ── */
  .section-count { display: inline-block; background: #dbeafe; color: #1e40af; padding: 1px 7px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 8px; font-weight: 600; margin-left: 6px; vertical-align: middle; }

  /* ── Audience Badge ── */
  .audience-badge { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 10px; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; margin-left: 12px; }
  .audience-executive { background: #dbeafe; color: #1e40af; }
  .audience-technical  { background: #dcfce7; color: #166534; }
  .audience-compliance { background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e; }

  /* ── Group Section Cards (grouped mode) ── */
  .group-card { border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 16px; page-break-inside: avoid; overflow: hidden; }
  .group-card-header { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f1f5f9, #e2e8f0); padding: 10px 14px; border-bottom: 2px solid #3b82f6; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; bookmark-level: 2; }
  .group-card-header h3 { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #0f172a; margin: 0; }
  .group-card-stats span { font-size: 8px; font-weight: 600; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; margin-left: 6px; }
  .group-card-stats .g-pass { background: #dcfce7; color: #166534; }
  .group-card-stats .g-fail { background: #fee2e2; color: #991b1b; }
  .group-summary { background: #eff6ff; border-left: 3px solid #3b82f6; padding: 8px 12px; margin: 8px 10px; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; font-size: 9.5px; line-height: 1.6; color: #334155; white-space: pre-wrap; }
  .group-summary-lbl { font-size: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.3px; color: #1e40af; margin-bottom: 4px; }

  /* ── Group Overview Table ── */
  .group-overview-tbl { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 9px; margin: 10px 0 16px; }
  .group-overview-tbl th { background: #f1f5f9; padding: 5px 6px; font-weight: 700; text-align: left; font-size: 8px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.3px; color: #475569; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; }
  .group-overview-tbl td { padding: 4px 6px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; }
  .group-overview-tbl tr:nth-child(even) { background: #f8fafc; }
  .group-overview-tbl .sev-cell { text-align: center; font-weight: 700; }
  .group-overview-tbl .sev-cell.has-val { color: #dc2626; }
  .group-overview-tbl .sev-cell.zero-val { color: #cbd5e1; }

  /* ── Severity Chips ── */
  .sev-chip { display: inline-block; font-size: 7.5px; padding: 1px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-weight: 700; margin-right: 3px; }
  .sev-chip-critical { background: #fee2e2; color: #991b1b; }
  .sev-chip-high { background: #ffedd5; color: #9a3412; }
  .sev-chip-medium { background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e; }
  .sev-chip-low { background: #dbeafe; color: #1e40af; }
  .sev-chip-informational { background: #f3f4f6; color: #374151; }

  /* ── False-Positive Suspect Styles ── */
  .fp-badge { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 8px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.3px; margin-left: 6px; }
  .fp-badge.fp-high { background: #fef2f2; color: #991b1b; border: 1px solid #fecaca; }
  .fp-badge.fp-medium { background: #fffbeb; color: #92400e; border: 1px solid #fde68a; }
  .fp-badge.fp-low { background: #eff6ff; color: #1e40af; border: 1px solid #bfdbfe; }
  .fp-analysis-box { background: #fefce8; border-left: 3px solid #eab308; padding: 4px 8px; margin: 4px 0; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; font-size: 8px; }
  .fp-signals { margin: 4px 0 0 12px; font-size: 8.5px; color: #64748b; }
  .fp-signals li { margin-bottom: 2px; }
  .fp-section-card { border: 1px solid #fde68a; border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px 14px; margin-bottom: 12px; background: #fffbeb; page-break-inside: avoid; }
  .fp-section-card h3 { font-size: 12px; color: #92400e; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .fp-stat-row { display: flex; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .fp-stat { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #fde68a; border-radius: 6px; padding: 8px 12px; text-align: center; flex: 1; }
  .fp-stat .val { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; }
  .fp-stat .lbl { font-size: 7px; color: #64748b; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ═══ Cover ═══ -->
<div class="cover">
  <div class="brand">AuditForge</div>
  <h1 style="bookmark-level: none;">{{ title or "Configuration Audit Report" }}</h1>
  <div class="subtitle">{{ mission_name }}</div>
  <div class="meta-block">
    <div class="meta-line"><strong>Client:</strong> {{ client_name }}</div>
    <div class="meta-line"><strong>Date Range:</strong> {{ date_range }}</div>
    <div class="meta-line"><strong>Generated:</strong> {{ generated_at }}</div>
    <div class="meta-line"><strong>Total Rules:</strong> {{ summary.total_rules }} &nbsp; | &nbsp; <strong>Compliance:</strong> {{ summary.overall_compliance }}%</div>
    {% if has_builder and audience %}<div class="meta-line"><strong>Audience:</strong> <span class="audience-badge audience-{{ audience }}">{{ audience }}</span></div>{% endif %}
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ Table of Contents (with page numbers via WeasyPrint target-counter) ═══ -->
{# Pre-count findings by status #}
{% set fail_count = namespace(val=0) %}
{% set error_count = namespace(val=0) %}
{% set pass_count = namespace(val=0) %}
{% for f in findings %}
  {% if f.status == "FAIL" %}{% set fail_count.val = fail_count.val + 1 %}
  {% elif f.status == "ERROR" %}{% set error_count.val = error_count.val + 1 %}
  {% elif f.status == "PASS" %}{% set pass_count.val = pass_count.val + 1 %}
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}

<div class="toc">
  <div class="toc-title">Table of Contents</div>
  <ul class="toc-list">
    {% set ns = namespace(n=1) %}

    {% if ai_summary %}
    <li><a href="#sec-ai-summary">{{ ns.n }}. AI Executive Summary</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}
    {% endif %}

    <li><a href="#sec-visual-dashboard">{{ ns.n }}. Visual Dashboard</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}

    <li><a href="#sec-executive-summary">{{ ns.n }}. Executive Summary &amp; Compliance Overview</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}

    <li><a href="#sec-audit-scope">{{ ns.n }}. Audit Scope</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}

    {% if by_category or (categories_enriched is defined and categories_enriched) %}
    <li><a href="#sec-by-category">{{ ns.n }}. Compliance by Category</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}
    {% endif %}

    {% if per_target_findings is defined and per_target_findings | length > 1 %}
    <li><a href="#sec-per-target">{{ ns.n }}. Per-Target Compliance Breakdown</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}
    {% endif %}

    <li><a href="#sec-methodology">{{ ns.n }}. Audit Methodology</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}

    <li><a href="#sec-findings-register">{{ ns.n }}. Complete Findings Register ({{ findings|length }})</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}

    {% if not section_toggles or section_toggles.get('recommendations', true) %}
    {% if recommendations is defined and recommendations %}
    <li><a href="#sec-recommendations">{{ ns.n }}. Prioritized Recommendations</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}
    {% endif %}
    {% endif %}

    {% if fp_summary and fp_summary.total_suspects is defined and fp_summary.total_suspects > 0 %}
    <li><a href="#sec-fp-analysis">{{ ns.n }}. False Positive Analysis</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}
    {% endif %}

    {% if has_builder and grouped_findings %}
    {# Builder mode: TOC entries for each group #}
    {% for group in grouped_findings %}
    <li><a href="#sec-group-{{ loop.index }}">{{ ns.n }}. {{ group.name }} ({{ group.findings|length }})</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}
    {% endfor %}
    {% else %}
    {# Default mode: severity-based TOC #}
    {% set ns_fail = ns.n %}
    <li><a href="#sec-failed-rules">{{ ns.n }}. Failed Rules ({{ fail_count.val }})</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}
    {# Sub-entries for severity groups within failed #}
    {% for sev in ["critical", "high", "medium", "low", "informational"] %}
      {% set sev_fail = namespace(val=0) %}
      {% for f in findings if f.status == "FAIL" and f.severity == sev %}{% set sev_fail.val = sev_fail.val + 1 %}{% endfor %}
      {% if sev_fail.val > 0 %}
      <li class="toc-sub"><a href="#sec-fail-{{ sev }}">{{ ns_fail }}.{{ loop.index }}. {{ sev | capitalize }} Severity ({{ sev_fail.val }})</a></li>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}

    {% if error_count.val > 0 %}
    <li><a href="#sec-error-rules">{{ ns.n }}. Errors ({{ error_count.val }})</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}
    {% endif %}

    {% if include_passed and pass_count.val > 0 %}
    <li><a href="#sec-passed-rules">{{ ns.n }}. Passed Rules ({{ pass_count.val }})</a></li>
    {% set ns.n = ns.n + 1 %}
    {% endif %}
    {% endif %}

    <li><a href="#sec-appendix">{{ ns.n }}. Appendix</a></li>
  </ul>
</div>

<!-- ═══ AI Executive Summary ═══ -->
{% if ai_summary %}
<div class="section" id="sec-ai-summary">
  <h2>AI Executive Summary</h2>
  <div class="ai-summary">{% if ai_summary_html %}{{ ai_summary_html|safe }}{% else %}{{ ai_summary }}{% endif %}</div>
</div>
{% endif %}

<!-- ═══ Visual Dashboard ═══ -->
{% if not section_toggles or section_toggles.get('charts', true) %}
<div class="section" id="sec-visual-dashboard">
  <h2>Visual Dashboard</h2>
  {# ── 2-column grid for paired charts ── #}
  <div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; justify-content: center; align-items: flex-start; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 12px 0;">
    {% if chart_donut %}<div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; max-width: 50%; text-align: center;">{{ chart_donut|safe }}</div>{% endif %}
    {% if chart_severity %}<div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; max-width: 50%; text-align: center;">{{ chart_severity|safe }}</div>{% endif %}
  </div>
  <div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; justify-content: center; align-items: flex-start; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 12px 0;">
    {% if chart_targets %}<div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; max-width: 50%; text-align: center;">{{ chart_targets|safe }}</div>{% endif %}
    {% if chart_categories %}<div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; max-width: 50%; text-align: center;">{{ chart_categories|safe }}</div>{% endif %}
  </div>
  {# ── Paired row: group compliance + FP gauge ── #}
  <div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; justify-content: center; align-items: flex-start; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 12px 0;">
    {% if chart_group_compliance %}<div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; max-width: 50%; text-align: center;">{{ chart_group_compliance|safe }}</div>{% endif %}
    {% if chart_fp_gauge %}<div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; max-width: 50%; text-align: center;">{{ chart_fp_gauge|safe }}</div>{% endif %}
  </div>
  {# ── Full-width charts ── #}
  {% if chart_risk_heatmap %}
  <div style="margin-top: 12px; text-align: center;">{{ chart_risk_heatmap|safe }}</div>
  {% endif %}
  <div style="display: flex; gap: 20px; justify-content: center; align-items: flex-start; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 12px 0;">
    {% if chart_radar %}<div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; max-width: 50%; text-align: center;">{{ chart_radar|safe }}</div>{% endif %}
    {% if chart_waterfall %}<div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; max-width: 50%; text-align: center;">{{ chart_waterfall|safe }}</div>{% endif %}
  </div>
  {% if chart_treemap %}
  <div style="margin-top: 12px; text-align: center;">{{ chart_treemap|safe }}</div>
  {% endif %}
</div>
{% endif %}

<!-- ═══ Executive Summary ═══ -->
{% if not section_toggles or section_toggles.get('executive_summary', true) %}
<div class="section" id="sec-executive-summary">
  <h2>Executive Summary &amp; Compliance Overview</h2>

  {# ── Risk Score Card ── #}
  {% if risk_score is defined and risk_score %}
  <div style="display: flex; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; align-items: stretch;">
    <div style="background: {{ risk_score.color }}15; border: 2px solid {{ risk_score.color }}; border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px 18px; text-align: center; min-width: 100px;">
      <div style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; color: {{ risk_score.color }};">{{ risk_score.grade }}</div>
      <div style="font-size: 8px; color: {{ risk_score.color }}; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;">{{ risk_score.label }}</div>
      <div style="font-size: 7px; color: #64748b; margin-top: 2px;">Risk Score: {{ risk_score.score }}%</div>
    </div>
    <div style="flex: 1;">
      <div class="stats" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="val">{{ summary.overall_compliance }}%</div>
          <div class="lbl">Compliance</div>
          <div class="compliance-bar">
            <div class="fill {% if summary.overall_compliance >= 80 %}fill-good{% elif summary.overall_compliance >= 50 %}fill-warn{% else %}fill-bad{% endif %}" style="width: {{ summary.overall_compliance }}%"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card"><div class="val">{{ summary.total_rules }}</div><div class="lbl">Total Rules</div></div>
        <div class="stat-card"><div class="val" style="color:#16a34a">{{ summary.passed }}</div><div class="lbl">Passed</div></div>
        <div class="stat-card"><div class="val" style="color:#dc2626">{{ summary.failed }}</div><div class="lbl">Failed</div></div>
        <div class="stat-card"><div class="val" style="color:#7c3aed">{{ summary.errors }}</div><div class="lbl">Errors</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p style="font-size: 8px; color: #64748b; margin-bottom: 8px;">
    <strong>Risk Level: {{ risk_score.risk_level }}</strong> — Score computed from compliance percentage weighted by severity of failures (Critical: 5×, High: 3×, Medium: 1×, Low: 0.3×).
  </p>
  {% else %}
  <div class="stats">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="val">{{ summary.overall_compliance }}%</div>
      <div class="lbl">Compliance</div>
      <div class="compliance-bar">
        <div class="fill {% if summary.overall_compliance >= 80 %}fill-good{% elif summary.overall_compliance >= 50 %}fill-warn{% else %}fill-bad{% endif %}" style="width: {{ summary.overall_compliance }}%"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="val">{{ summary.total_rules }}</div><div class="lbl">Total Rules</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="val" style="color:#16a34a">{{ summary.passed }}</div><div class="lbl">Passed</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="val" style="color:#dc2626">{{ summary.failed }}</div><div class="lbl">Failed</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="val" style="color:#7c3aed">{{ summary.errors }}</div><div class="lbl">Errors</div></div>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <h3>Findings by Severity</h3>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Severity</th><th>Total</th><th>Passed</th><th>Failed</th><th>Compliance</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for sev in ["critical", "high", "medium", "low", "informational"] %}
      {% set info = summary.by_severity.get(sev, {"total": 0, "passed": 0, "failed": 0}) %}
      <tr>
        <td><span class="badge sev-{{ sev }}">{{ sev | upper }}</span></td>
        <td>{{ info.total }}</td>
        <td>{{ info.passed }}</td>
        <td>{{ info.failed }}</td>
        <td>
          {{ "%.1f" | format(info.passed / info.total * 100) if info.total > 0 else "0.0" }}%
          <div class="compliance-bar">
            {% set comp = (info.passed / info.total * 100) if info.total > 0 else 0 %}
            <div class="fill {% if comp >= 80 %}fill-good{% elif comp >= 50 %}fill-warn{% else %}fill-bad{% endif %}" style="width: {{ comp }}%"></div>
          </div>
        </td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  {# ── Top 10 Critical / High Findings (upgraded from 5) ── #}
  {% set top10 = namespace(items=[]) %}
  {% for f in findings if f.status == "FAIL" and f.severity in ["critical", "high"] %}
    {% if top10.items | length < 10 %}
      {% set top10.items = top10.items + [f] %}
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
  {# Fall back to medium if fewer than 5 critical/high #}
  {% if top10.items | length < 5 %}
    {% for f in findings if f.status == "FAIL" and f.severity == "medium" %}
      {% if top10.items | length < 10 %}
        {% set top10.items = top10.items + [f] %}
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  {% endif %}
  {% if top10.items %}
  <h3>Top Critical / High Findings</h3>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Section</th><th>Rule</th><th>Severity</th><th>Target</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for f in top10.items %}
      <tr>
        <td style="font-weight:600; text-align:center;">{{ loop.index }}</td>
        <td><a href="#finding-{{ f.section_number | replace('.', '-') }}" style="color:#1e40af;text-decoration:none;">{{ f.section_number }}</a></td>
        <td>{{ f.rule_title }}</td>
        <td><span class="badge sev-{{ f.severity }}">{{ f.severity | upper }}</span></td>
        <td>{{ f.target_hostname }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% endif %}
</div>
{% endif %}

<!-- ═══ Audit Scope ═══ -->
<div class="section" id="sec-audit-scope">
  <h2>Audit Scope</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Target</th><th>IP Address</th><th>Type</th><th>OS</th><th>Benchmark</th><th>Compliance</th><th>Scan Date</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for t in targets %}
        {% for s in t.scans %}
        <tr>
          <td>{{ t.hostname }}</td>
          <td>{{ t.ip_address }}</td>
          <td>{{ t.target_type }}</td>
          <td>{{ t.os_details }}</td>
          <td>{{ s.benchmark_name }}</td>
          <td>
            {{ s.compliance_percentage }}%
            <div class="compliance-bar">
              <div class="fill {% if s.compliance_percentage >= 80 %}fill-good{% elif s.compliance_percentage >= 50 %}fill-warn{% else %}fill-bad{% endif %}" style="width: {{ s.compliance_percentage }}%"></div>
            </div>
          </td>
          <td>{{ s.completed_at }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<!-- ═══ Compliance by Category (enriched CIS section names) ═══ -->
{% if categories_enriched is defined and categories_enriched %}
<div class="section" id="sec-by-category">
  <h2>Compliance by Category</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Section</th><th>Category Name</th><th>Total</th><th>Passed</th><th>Failed</th><th>Compliance</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for cat in categories_enriched %}
      <tr{% if cat.compliance < 50 %} style="background:#fef2f2"{% elif cat.compliance < 80 %} style="background:#fffbeb"{% endif %}>
        <td style="font-weight:600; text-align:center;">{{ cat.key }}</td>
        <td style="font-weight:600">{{ cat.label }}</td>
        <td>{{ cat.total }}</td>
        <td style="color:#16a34a;font-weight:600">{{ cat.passed }}</td>
        <td style="color:#dc2626;font-weight:600">{{ cat.failed }}</td>
        <td>
          {{ "%.1f" | format(cat.compliance) }}%
          <div class="compliance-bar">
            <div class="fill {% if cat.compliance >= 80 %}fill-good{% elif cat.compliance >= 50 %}fill-warn{% else %}fill-bad{% endif %}" style="width: {{ cat.compliance }}%"></div>
          </div>
        </td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
{% elif by_category %}
<div class="section" id="sec-by-category">
  <h2>Compliance by Category</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Category</th><th>Total</th><th>Passed</th><th>Failed</th><th>Compliance</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for cat_key in by_category.keys() | sort %}
      {% set info = by_category[cat_key] %}
      {% set comp = (info.passed / info.total * 100) | round(1) if info.total > 0 else 0.0 %}
      <tr>
        <td style="font-weight:600">{{ info.get('label', 'Section ' ~ cat_key) }}</td>
        <td>{{ info.total }}</td>
        <td style="color:#16a34a;font-weight:600">{{ info.passed }}</td>
        <td style="color:#dc2626;font-weight:600">{{ info.failed }}</td>
        <td>
          {{ comp }}%
          <div class="compliance-bar">
            <div class="fill {% if comp >= 80 %}fill-good{% elif comp >= 50 %}fill-warn{% else %}fill-bad{% endif %}" style="width: {{ comp }}%"></div>
          </div>
        </td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
{% endif %}

<!-- ═══ Per-Target Breakdown ═══ -->
{% if per_target_findings is defined and per_target_findings | length > 1 %}
<div class="section" id="sec-per-target" style="page-break-before: always;">
  <h2>Per-Target Compliance Breakdown</h2>
  <p style="font-size: 8px; color: #64748b; margin-bottom: 8px;">Individual compliance status for each audited target, sorted from lowest to highest compliance.</p>

  {% for target in per_target_findings %}
  <div style="border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; border-radius: 6px; padding: 8px 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;{% if target.compliance < 50 %} border-left: 3px solid #dc2626;{% elif target.compliance < 80 %} border-left: 3px solid #f59e0b;{% else %} border-left: 3px solid #16a34a;{% endif %}">
    <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 6px;">
      <h3 style="margin: 0; font-size: 10px; color: #1e3a5f;">{{ target.hostname }}</h3>
      <span style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; color: {% if target.compliance >= 80 %}#16a34a{% elif target.compliance >= 50 %}#f59e0b{% else %}#dc2626{% endif %};">
        {{ "%.1f" | format(target.compliance) }}%
      </span>
    </div>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 8px; font-size: 8px; margin-bottom: 6px;">
      <span>Total: <strong>{{ target.total }}</strong></span>
      <span style="color:#16a34a">Pass: <strong>{{ target.passed }}</strong></span>
      <span style="color:#dc2626">Fail: <strong>{{ target.failed }}</strong></span>
      <span style="color:#7c3aed">Error: <strong>{{ target.errors }}</strong></span>
      {% if target.critical_fails > 0 %}<span style="color:#7f1d1d">Critical Fails: <strong>{{ target.critical_fails }}</strong></span>{% endif %}
      {% if target.high_fails > 0 %}<span style="color:#991b1b">High Fails: <strong>{{ target.high_fails }}</strong></span>{% endif %}
    </div>
    <div class="compliance-bar" style="height: 6px;">
      <div class="fill {% if target.compliance >= 80 %}fill-good{% elif target.compliance >= 50 %}fill-warn{% else %}fill-bad{% endif %}" style="width: {{ target.compliance }}%"></div>
    </div>
    {% if target.top_failures %}
    <p style="font-size: 7px; color: #64748b; margin: 4px 0 2px;">Top failures:</p>
    <div style="font-size: 7px; color: #475569;">
      {% for fail in target.top_failures %}
      <span style="display: inline-block; background: #fef2f2; border-radius: 3px; padding: 1px 4px; margin: 1px;">{{ fail.section_number }} — {{ fail.rule_title[:60] }}{% if fail.rule_title | length > 60 %}…{% endif %}</span>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
{% endif %}

<!-- ═══ Audit Methodology ═══ -->
<div class="section" id="sec-methodology">
  <h2>Audit Methodology</h2>
  <h3>Approach</h3>
  <p style="font-size: 8px; color: #334155; line-height: 1.5;">
    This audit was conducted using <strong>AuditForge</strong>, an automated compliance assessment platform.
    Each rule from the selected CIS Benchmark was evaluated against the target system(s) using
    registry queries, security policy exports, PowerShell commands, and WMI/CIM queries executed
    via WinRM (Windows Remote Management) or local execution.
  </p>
  <h3>Scoring Criteria</h3>
  <table style="font-size: 8px;">
    <thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><span class="badge" style="background:#dcfce7; color:#166534;">PASS</span></td><td>The system configuration matches the benchmark recommendation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge" style="background:#fef2f2; color:#991b1b;">FAIL</span></td><td>The system configuration does NOT meet the benchmark recommendation and requires remediation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge" style="background:#f3e8ff; color:#6b21a8;">ERROR</span></td><td>The audit check could not be completed (access denied, registry key missing, WinRM failure, etc.). Manual verification is required.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <h3>Severity Levels</h3>
  <table style="font-size: 8px;">
    <thead><tr><th>Level</th><th>Definition</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><span class="badge sev-critical">CRITICAL</span></td><td>Immediate risk of exploitation. Must be remediated within 24-72 hours.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge sev-high">HIGH</span></td><td>Significant security weakness. Remediate within 1-2 weeks.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge sev-medium">MEDIUM</span></td><td>Moderate risk. Remediate within 30 days as part of regular patching cycles.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge sev-low">LOW</span></td><td>Minor hardening opportunity. Address during next maintenance window.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge sev-informational">INFO</span></td><td>Best practice recommendation with minimal direct security impact.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <h3>Risk Score Calculation</h3>
  <p style="font-size: 8px; color: #334155; line-height: 1.5;">
    The overall risk score combines the raw compliance percentage with a severity-weighted penalty:
    <br><code style="font-size: 7px; background: #f1f5f9; padding: 2px 4px; border-radius: 3px;">
    Score = Compliance% − (Critical×5 + High×3 + Medium×1 + Low×0.3) ÷ TotalRules × 10
    </code><br>
    Grades: <strong>A</strong> (≥90), <strong>B</strong> (≥75), <strong>C</strong> (≥60), <strong>D</strong> (≥40), <strong>F</strong> (&lt;40).
  </p>
</div>

<!-- ═══ Complete Findings Register (master table of ALL rules) ═══ -->
<div class="section" id="sec-findings-register" style="page-break-before: always;">
  <h2>Complete Findings Register <span class="section-count">{{ findings|length }}</span></h2>
  <p style="font-size: 8px; color: #64748b; margin-bottom: 6px;">Comprehensive list of every audited rule, sorted by section number. Click a section number to jump to the detailed finding.</p>
  <table style="font-size: 7.5px;">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th style="width:7%">#</th>
        <th style="width:8%">Section</th>
        <th style="width:37%">Rule Title</th>
        <th style="width:10%">Severity</th>
        <th style="width:8%">Status</th>
        <th style="width:15%">Target</th>
        <th style="width:15%">Benchmark</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for f in findings %}
      <tr style="{% if f.status == 'FAIL' and f.severity == 'critical' %}background:#fef2f2{% elif f.status == 'FAIL' and f.severity == 'high' %}background:#fff7ed{% elif f.status == 'ERROR' %}background:#faf5ff{% endif %}">
        <td style="text-align:center; color:#94a3b8;">{{ loop.index }}</td>
        <td style="font-weight:600;white-space:nowrap"><a href="#finding-{{ f.section_number | replace('.', '-') }}" style="color:#1e40af;text-decoration:none;">{{ f.section_number }}</a></td>
        <td>{{ f.rule_title }}</td>
        <td><span class="badge sev-{{ f.severity }}" style="font-size:7px;padding:1px 5px">{{ f.severity | upper }}</span></td>
        <td><span class="badge st-{{ f.status | lower }}" style="font-size:7px;padding:1px 5px">{{ f.status }}</span></td>
        <td style="font-size:7px">{{ f.target_hostname }}</td>
        <td style="font-size:7px">{{ f.benchmark_name }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<!-- ═══ Prioritized Recommendations ═══ -->
{% if not section_toggles or section_toggles.get('recommendations', true) %}
{% if recommendations is defined and recommendations %}
<div class="section" id="sec-recommendations" style="page-break-before: always;">
  <h2>Prioritized Remediation Recommendations</h2>
  <p style="font-size: 8.5px; color: #475569; margin-bottom: 8px;">
    The following remediation actions are prioritized by severity (critical first). Each recommendation addresses one or more failed audit rules.
  </p>

  {% set rec_sev_shown = namespace(current="") %}
  {% set rec_count = namespace(n=0) %}
  {% for f in recommendations %}
    {% if f.remediation %}
    {% if f.severity != rec_sev_shown.current %}
      {% set rec_sev_shown.current = f.severity %}
      <div class="severity-group-header sev-bg-{{ f.severity }}" style="margin-top:10px;">
        <span>{{ f.severity | upper }} SEVERITY RECOMMENDATIONS</span>
      </div>
    {% endif %}
    {% set rec_count.n = rec_count.n + 1 %}
    <div style="border-left: 3px solid {% if f.severity == 'critical' %}#dc2626{% elif f.severity == 'high' %}#ea580c{% elif f.severity == 'medium' %}#d97706{% elif f.severity == 'low' %}#2563eb{% else %}#6b7280{% endif %}; padding: 4px 8px; margin: 4px 0; page-break-inside: avoid; background: #fafbfc; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;">
      <p style="font-size: 8.5px; margin: 1px 0;"><strong style="color: #0f172a;">{{ rec_count.n }}. [{{ f.section_number }}] {{ f.rule_title }}</strong></p>
      <p style="font-size: 8px; color: #475569; margin: 1px 0;">{{ f.remediation }}</p>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}

  {% if rec_count.n == 0 %}
  <p style="font-size: 9px; color: #16a34a; font-weight: 600;">No failed rules with remediation actions found.</p>
  {% endif %}
</div>
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

<!-- ═══ False Positive Analysis ═══ -->
{% if fp_summary and fp_summary.total_suspects is defined and fp_summary.total_suspects > 0 %}
<div class="section" id="sec-fp-analysis">
  <h2>False Positive Analysis</h2>
  <div class="fp-section-card">
    <h3>⚠ Potential False Positives Detected</h3>
    <p style="font-size: 9.5px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #475569;">
      The intelligent analysis engine has identified <strong>{{ fp_summary.total_suspects }}</strong> finding(s) that may be false positives.
      These should be reviewed by an auditor before finalizing the report.
    </p>
    <div class="fp-stat-row">
      <div class="fp-stat"><div class="val" style="color:#dc2626">{{ fp_summary.high_confidence }}</div><div class="lbl">High Confidence</div></div>
      <div class="fp-stat"><div class="val" style="color:#d97706">{{ fp_summary.medium_confidence }}</div><div class="lbl">Medium Confidence</div></div>
      <div class="fp-stat"><div class="val" style="color:#3b82f6">{{ fp_summary.low_confidence }}</div><div class="lbl">Low Confidence</div></div>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size: 10px; margin-top: 12px;">Suspect Findings Detail</h3>
    <table style="font-size: 9px;">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Section</th><th>Rule</th><th>Severity</th><th>FP Confidence</th><th>Primary Reason</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for f in findings if f.status == "FAIL" and f.fp_analysis is defined and f.fp_analysis.is_suspect %}
        <tr>
          <td>{{ f.section_number }}</td>
          <td>{{ f.rule_title }}</td>
          <td><span class="badge sev-{{ f.severity }}">{{ f.severity | upper }}</span></td>
          <td>
            <span class="fp-badge fp-{{ f.fp_analysis.confidence_label | lower }}">
              {{ f.fp_analysis.confidence_label }} ({{ f.fp_analysis.confidence }}%)
            </span>
          </td>
          <td style="font-size: 8.5px; color: #64748b;">{{ f.fp_analysis.top_reason }}</td>
        </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
{% endif %}

{% if has_builder and grouped_findings %}
<!-- ═══ Builder Mode — Group Overview Summary ═══ -->
<div class="section">
  <h2>Group Overview</h2>
  <table class="group-overview-tbl">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Group</th><th>Total</th><th>Passed</th><th>Failed</th><th>Errors</th>
        <th style="text-align:center">CRIT</th><th style="text-align:center">HIGH</th>
        <th style="text-align:center">MED</th><th style="text-align:center">LOW</th>
        <th style="text-align:center">INFO</th>
        <th>Compliance</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for group in grouped_findings %}
      <tr>
        <td style="font-weight:700">{{ group.name }}</td>
        <td>{{ group.total_count }}</td>
        <td style="color:#16a34a;font-weight:700">{{ group.pass_count }}</td>
        <td style="color:#dc2626;font-weight:700">{{ group.fail_count }}</td>
        <td style="color:#7c3aed">{{ group.error_count }}</td>
        {% for sev in ["critical", "high", "medium", "low", "informational"] %}
        {% set sc = group.sev_counts.get(sev, 0) %}
        <td class="sev-cell {{ 'has-val' if sc > 0 else 'zero-val' }}">{{ sc }}</td>
        {% endfor %}
        <td>
          <strong style="{% if group.compliance_pct >= 80 %}color:#16a34a{% elif group.compliance_pct >= 50 %}color:#d97706{% else %}color:#dc2626{% endif %}">{{ group.compliance_pct }}%</strong>
          <div class="compliance-bar">
            <div class="fill {% if group.compliance_pct >= 80 %}fill-good{% elif group.compliance_pct >= 50 %}fill-warn{% else %}fill-bad{% endif %}" style="width:{{ group.compliance_pct }}%"></div>
          </div>
        </td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<!-- ═══ Builder Mode — Grouped Findings ═══ -->
{% for group in grouped_findings %}
<div class="section group-card" id="sec-group-{{ loop.index }}">
  <div class="group-card-header">
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;">
      {% if group.mini_donut %}{{ group.mini_donut|safe }}{% endif %}
      <div>
        <h2 style="margin:0">{{ group.name }}</h2>
        <span style="font-size:8px;color:#64748b">{{ group.total_count }} rules - {{ group.compliance_pct }}% compliant</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="group-card-stats">
      <span class="g-pass" style="font-size:8px;font-weight:700;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:4px;background:#dcfce7;color:#166534">{{ group.pass_count }} Passed</span>
      <span class="g-fail" style="font-size:8px;font-weight:700;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:4px;background:#fee2e2;color:#991b1b">{{ group.fail_count }} Failed</span>
      {% if group.error_count > 0 %}
      <span style="font-size:8px;font-weight:700;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:4px;background:#f3e8ff;color:#6b21a8">{{ group.error_count }} Errors</span>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>

  {% if group.sev_detail %}
  <div style="padding:4px 10px;">
    {% for sev in ["critical", "high", "medium", "low", "informational"] %}
      {% if group.sev_detail.get(sev) %}
      {% set sd = group.sev_detail[sev] %}
      <span class="sev-chip sev-chip-{{ sev }}">{{ sev|upper }}: {{ sd.failed }}F / {{ sd.passed }}P</span>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  {% if group.summary %}
  <div class="group-summary">
    <span class="group-summary-lbl">AI Group Summary</span>
    {{ group.summary }}
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  {% if not section_toggles or section_toggles.get('findings_detail', true) %}
  {% for f in group.findings %}
  <div class="finding-card sev-border-{{ f.severity }}" id="finding-{{ f.section_number | replace('.', '-') }}">
    <div class="header">
      <span class="rule-id">{{ f.section_number }} - {{ f.rule_title }}</span>
      <span>
        <span class="badge sev-{{ f.severity }}">{{ f.severity | upper }}</span>
        <span class="badge st-{{ f.status | lower }}">{{ f.status }}</span>
        {% if f.fp_analysis is defined and f.fp_analysis.is_suspect %}
        <span class="fp-badge fp-{{ f.fp_analysis.confidence_label | lower }}">⚠ FP {{ f.fp_analysis.confidence_label }}</span>
        {% endif %}
      </span>
    </div>
    {% if f.fp_analysis is defined and f.fp_analysis.is_suspect %}
    <div class="fp-analysis-box">
      <strong>⚠ Potential False Positive ({{ f.fp_analysis.confidence }}% confidence):</strong> {{ f.fp_analysis.top_reason }}
      {% if f.fp_analysis.signal_count > 1 %}
      <ul class="fp-signals">
        {% for sig in f.fp_analysis.signals %}
        <li>{{ sig.reason }} ({{ sig.confidence }}%)</li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    {% endif %}
    {% if f.description %}<p><span class="field-label">Description:</span> {{ f.description }}</p>{% endif %}
    {% if f.rationale %}
    <div class="rationale-box"><strong>Rationale:</strong> {{ f.rationale }}</div>
    {% endif %}
    <p><span class="field-label">Expected:</span> <code>{{ f.expected_output_display|default(f.expected_output, true) }}</code>{% if f.expected_output_truncated %}<span style="color:#64748b; font-style:italic; font-size:7.5px;"> ({{ f.expected_output_length }} chars)</span>{% endif %}</p>
    <p><span class="field-label">Actual:</span> <code class="output-val">{{ f.actual_output_display|default(f.actual_output, true) }}</code>{% if f.actual_output_truncated %}<span style="color:#64748b; font-style:italic; font-size:7.5px;"> ({{ f.actual_output_length }} chars{% if f.actual_output_lines_hidden %}, {{ f.actual_output_lines_hidden }} lines hidden{% endif %})</span>{% endif %}</p>
    {% if f.evaluation_explanation %}
    <div class="eval-box"><strong>Evaluation:</strong> {{ f.evaluation_explanation }}</div>
    {% endif %}
    {% if not section_toggles or section_toggles.get('recommendations', true) %}
    {% if f.remediation %}<p><span class="field-label">Remediation:</span> {{ f.remediation }}</p>{% endif %}
    {% if f.ai_advice %}
    <div class="ai-advice-box"><strong>AI Advice:</strong> {{ f.ai_advice }}</div>
    {% endif %}
    {% endif %}
    {% if f.default_value %}<p><span class="field-label">Default Value:</span> <code>{{ f.default_value }}</code></p>{% endif %}
    {% if f.auditor_notes %}<p><span class="field-label">Notes:</span> {{ f.auditor_notes }}</p>{% endif %}
    {% if f.auditor_override %}<p><span class="field-label">Override:</span> {{ f.auditor_override }}</p>{% endif %}
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
  {% endif %}
</div>
{% endfor %}

{% else %}
<!-- ═══ Default Mode — Failed Rules Grouped by Severity ═══ -->
{% if not section_toggles or section_toggles.get('findings_detail', true) %}
<div class="section" id="sec-failed-rules" style="page-break-before: always;">
  <h2>Failed Rules — Detailed Analysis <span class="section-count">{{ fail_count.val }}</span></h2>
  <p style="font-size: 8px; color: #64748b; margin-bottom: 6px;">Each finding includes the rule description, expected vs. actual configuration values, evaluation results, and remediation guidance.</p>

  {% for sev in ["critical", "high", "medium", "low", "informational"] %}
    {% set sev_findings = [] %}
    {% for f in findings if f.status == "FAIL" and f.severity == sev %}
      {% if sev_findings.append(f) %}{% endif %}
    {% endfor %}

    {% if sev_findings | length > 0 %}
    <div id="sec-fail-{{ sev }}" {% if not loop.first %}style="page-break-before: always;"{% endif %}>
      <div class="severity-group-header sev-bg-{{ sev }}">
        <span>{{ sev | upper }} SEVERITY</span>
        <span class="count-badge">{{ sev_findings | length }} rule{{ 's' if sev_findings | length != 1 else '' }}</span>
      </div>

      {% for f in sev_findings %}
      <div class="finding-card sev-border-{{ f.severity }}" id="finding-{{ f.section_number | replace('.', '-') }}">
        <div class="header">
          <span class="rule-id">{{ f.section_number }} - {{ f.rule_title }}</span>
          <span>
            <span class="badge sev-{{ f.severity }}">{{ f.severity | upper }}</span>
            <span class="badge st-fail">FAIL</span>
            {% if f.fp_analysis is defined and f.fp_analysis.is_suspect %}
            <span class="fp-badge fp-{{ f.fp_analysis.confidence_label | lower }}">⚠ FP {{ f.fp_analysis.confidence_label }}</span>
            {% endif %}
          </span>
        </div>
        {% if f.fp_analysis is defined and f.fp_analysis.is_suspect %}
        <div class="fp-analysis-box">
          <strong>⚠ Potential False Positive ({{ f.fp_analysis.confidence }}% confidence):</strong> {{ f.fp_analysis.top_reason }}
          {% if f.fp_analysis.signal_count > 1 %}
          <ul class="fp-signals">
            {% for sig in f.fp_analysis.signals %}
            <li>{{ sig.reason }} ({{ sig.confidence }}%)</li>
            {% endfor %}
          </ul>
          {% endif %}
        </div>
        {% endif %}
        {% if f.description %}<p><span class="field-label">Description:</span> {{ f.description }}</p>{% endif %}
        {% if f.rationale %}
        <div class="rationale-box"><strong>Rationale:</strong> {{ f.rationale }}</div>
        {% endif %}
        <p><span class="field-label">Expected:</span> <code>{{ f.expected_output_display|default(f.expected_output, true) }}</code>{% if f.expected_output_truncated %}<span style="color:#64748b; font-style:italic; font-size:7.5px;"> ({{ f.expected_output_length }} chars)</span>{% endif %}</p>
        <p><span class="field-label">Actual:</span> <code class="output-val">{{ f.actual_output_display|default(f.actual_output, true) }}</code>{% if f.actual_output_truncated %}<span style="color:#64748b; font-style:italic; font-size:7.5px;"> ({{ f.actual_output_length }} chars{% if f.actual_output_lines_hidden %}, {{ f.actual_output_lines_hidden }} lines hidden{% endif %})</span>{% endif %}</p>
        {% if f.evaluation_explanation %}
        <div class="eval-box"><strong>Evaluation:</strong> {{ f.evaluation_explanation }}</div>
        {% endif %}
        {% if f.remediation %}<p><span class="field-label">Remediation:</span> {{ f.remediation }}</p>{% endif %}
        {% if f.ai_advice %}
        <div class="ai-advice-box"><strong>AI Advice:</strong> {{ f.ai_advice }}</div>
        {% endif %}
        {% if f.default_value %}<p><span class="field-label">Default Value:</span> <code>{{ f.default_value }}</code></p>{% endif %}
        {% if f.auditor_notes %}<p><span class="field-label">Notes:</span> {{ f.auditor_notes }}</p>{% endif %}
        {% if f.auditor_override %}<p><span class="field-label">Override:</span> {{ f.auditor_override }}</p>{% endif %}
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
</div>
{% else %}
{# findings_detail is disabled — show compact failed rules table instead #}
<div class="section" id="sec-failed-rules" style="page-break-before: always;">
  <h2>Failed Rules Summary <span class="section-count">{{ fail_count.val }}</span></h2>
  <table style="font-size: 8px;">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Section</th><th>Rule Title</th><th>Severity</th><th>Target</th><th>Expected</th><th>Actual</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for f in findings if f.status == "FAIL" %}
      <tr>
        <td style="font-weight:600;white-space:nowrap">{{ f.section_number }}</td>
        <td>{{ f.rule_title }}</td>
        <td><span class="badge sev-{{ f.severity }}" style="font-size:7px;padding:1px 4px">{{ f.severity | upper }}</span></td>
        <td style="font-size:7px">{{ f.target_hostname }}</td>
        <td style="font-size:7px;max-width:100px;overflow:hidden;text-overflow:ellipsis"><code>{{ f.expected_output[:80] }}</code></td>
        <td style="font-size:7px;max-width:100px;overflow:hidden;text-overflow:ellipsis"><code>{{ f.actual_output[:80] }}</code></td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
{% endif %}

<!-- ═══ Errors Section ═══ -->
{% set error_findings = [] %}
{% for f in findings if f.status == "ERROR" %}
  {% if error_findings.append(f) %}{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% if error_findings | length > 0 %}
<div class="section" id="sec-error-rules" style="page-break-before: always;">
  <h2>Errors <span class="section-count">{{ error_findings | length }}</span></h2>
  <p style="font-size: 8px; color: #64748b; margin-bottom: 6px;">Rules that encountered execution errors during the audit. These require investigation — the rule may need command correction or the target may have access issues.</p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Section</th><th>Rule</th><th>Severity</th><th>Target</th><th>Error Output</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for f in error_findings %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ f.section_number }}</td>
        <td>{{ f.rule_title }}</td>
        <td><span class="badge sev-{{ f.severity }}">{{ f.severity | upper }}</span></td>
        <td>{{ f.target_hostname }}</td>
        <td style="max-width: 200px; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap;"><code>{{ f.actual_output[:120] }}</code></td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
{% endif %}

<!-- ═══ Passed Rules — Full Detail ═══ -->
{% if include_passed %}
{% set passed_findings = [] %}
{% for f in findings if f.status == "PASS" %}
  {% if passed_findings.append(f) %}{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% if passed_findings | length > 0 %}
<div class="section" id="sec-passed-rules" style="page-break-before: always;">
  <h2>Passed Rules <span class="section-count">{{ passed_findings | length }}</span></h2>
  <p style="font-size: 8px; color: #64748b; margin-bottom: 8px;">Rules that met the expected CIS benchmark configuration. Grouped by severity for reference.</p>

  {% for sev in ["critical", "high", "medium", "low", "informational"] %}
    {% set sev_passed = [] %}
    {% for f in passed_findings if f.severity == sev %}
      {% if sev_passed.append(f) %}{% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
    {% if sev_passed | length > 0 %}
    <div class="severity-group-header sev-bg-{{ sev }}" style="opacity: 0.85;">
      <span>{{ sev | upper }} — PASSED</span>
      <span class="count-badge">{{ sev_passed | length }} rule{{ 's' if sev_passed | length != 1 else '' }}</span>
    </div>

    {% for f in sev_passed %}
    <div class="finding-card sev-border-{{ f.severity }}" id="finding-{{ f.section_number | replace('.', '-') }}" style="border-left-color: #22c55e;">
      <div class="header">
        <span class="rule-id">{{ f.section_number }} — {{ f.rule_title }}</span>
        <span>
          <span class="badge sev-{{ f.severity }}">{{ f.severity | upper }}</span>
          <span class="badge st-pass">PASS</span>
        </span>
      </div>
      {% if f.description %}<p><span class="field-label">Description:</span> {{ f.description }}</p>{% endif %}
      <p><span class="field-label">Expected:</span> <code>{{ f.expected_output }}</code></p>
      <p><span class="field-label">Actual:</span> <code>{{ f.actual_output }}</code></p>
      {% if f.evaluation_explanation %}
      <div class="eval-box"><strong>Evaluation:</strong> {{ f.evaluation_explanation }}</div>
      {% endif %}
      {% if f.default_value %}<p><span class="field-label">Default Value:</span> <code>{{ f.default_value }}</code></p>{% endif %}
      {% if f.auditor_notes %}<p><span class="field-label">Notes:</span> {{ f.auditor_notes }}</p>{% endif %}
      {% if f.auditor_override %}<p><span class="field-label">Override:</span> {{ f.auditor_override }}</p>{% endif %}
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
</div>
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

<!-- ═══ Compliance Trend (placeholder) ═══ -->
<div class="section" id="sec-compliance-trend">
  <h2>Compliance Trend</h2>
  <div style="border: 1px dashed #cbd5e1; border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; text-align: center; color: #94a3b8;">
    <p style="font-size: 10px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 4px;">Historical Trend Data Not Yet Available</p>
    <p style="font-size: 8px;">When multiple scans of the same target are completed, a compliance trend chart will appear here showing progress over time.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ Appendix ═══ -->
<div class="section" id="sec-appendix" style="page-break-before: always;">
  <h2>Appendix</h2>

  <h3>A. Benchmark Information</h3>
  <table style="font-size: 8px;">
    <tbody>
      {% if audit_info is defined and audit_info %}
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600; width:30%;">Benchmark</td><td>{{ audit_info.get('benchmark_name', 'N/A') }}</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">Version</td><td>{{ audit_info.get('benchmark_version', 'N/A') }}</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">Profile Level</td><td>{{ audit_info.get('profile_level', 'N/A') }}</td></tr>
      {% endif %}
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">Total Rules Evaluated</td><td>{{ summary.total_rules }}</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">Report Generated</td><td>{{ now }}</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">Engine</td><td>AuditForge — Automated CIS Compliance Auditing Platform</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>B. Glossary of Terms</h3>
  <table style="font-size: 8px;">
    <thead><tr><th style="width:25%;">Term</th><th>Definition</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">CIS Benchmark</td><td>Configuration guidelines published by the Center for Internet Security (CIS) for hardening operating systems, applications, and network devices.</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">Compliance %</td><td>Percentage of audited rules that PASS relative to the total number of rules evaluated (excluding errors unless noted).</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">Remediation</td><td>The corrective action required to bring a system setting into compliance with the benchmark recommendation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">Registry Key</td><td>A Windows Registry entry that stores OS and application configuration settings. Many CIS rules validate specific registry values.</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">Security Policy (secedit)</td><td>Windows Local Security Policy settings exported via <code>secedit.exe</code>. Includes password, lockout, and audit policies.</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">WinRM</td><td>Windows Remote Management — a Microsoft protocol for remote administration used by AuditForge to execute audit checks on target machines.</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="font-weight:600;">Risk Score</td><td>A weighted metric combining compliance percentage with severity-adjusted failure penalties, producing a letter grade (A–F).</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>C. Status Codes Reference</h3>
  <table style="font-size: 8px;">
    <thead><tr><th>Code</th><th>Color</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><span class="badge" style="background:#dcfce7; color:#166534;">PASS</span></td><td style="color:#16a34a;">Green</td><td>System matches benchmark expectation</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge" style="background:#fef2f2; color:#991b1b;">FAIL</span></td><td style="color:#dc2626;">Red</td><td>System does NOT match — remediation needed</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge" style="background:#f3e8ff; color:#6b21a8;">ERROR</span></td><td style="color:#7c3aed;">Purple</td><td>Check could not complete — manual review required</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>


</div>

</body>
</html>
